.\" Man page for btrfs-backup-ng transfer
.TH BTRFS-BACKUP-NG-TRANSFER 1 "January 2026" "btrfs-backup-ng" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
btrfs-backup-ng-transfer \- transfer existing snapshots to targets
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B btrfs-backup-ng transfer
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
Transfer existing snapshots to configured targets without creating new ones.
Uses incremental transfers when possible for efficiency.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-dry-run
Show what would be done without making any changes.
.TP
.BI \-\-volume " PATH"
Only transfer the specified volume(s). Can be specified multiple times.
.TP
.BI \-\-compress " METHOD"
Compression method for transfers. Overrides per-target configuration.
Valid methods: none, zstd, gzip, lz4, pigz, lzop.
.TP
.BI \-\-rate-limit " RATE"
Bandwidth limit for transfers. Examples: 10M, 1G, 500K.
.TP
.B \-\-progress
Show progress bars during transfers.
.TP
.B \-\-no-progress
Disable progress bars.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Transfer all pending snapshots:
.B btrfs-backup-ng transfer
.TP
Transfer with compression:
.B btrfs-backup-ng transfer --compress zstd
.TP
Transfer specific volume with rate limiting:
.B btrfs-backup-ng transfer --volume /home --rate-limit 50M
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR btrfs-backup-ng (1),
